====Noun====
{{en-noun|s}}

# In [[Arabic]] [[script]], the [[vowel]] point for "[[a]]", appearing as a [[diagonal]] [[line]] placed above a letter and designating a short /a/: {{Arab|[[ـَ]]}}.
#: Example: {{Arab|دَ}} /da/.
#:: If the Arabic letters {{Arab|[[ا]]}} (ʾalif) or {{Arab|[[ى]]}} (ʾalif maqṣūra) immediately follow, it indicates a long /ā/.
#::: Example: {{Arab|دَا}} or {{Arab|دَى}} /dā/ [daː].
# The vowel designated by this mark.

